other_tests.findings: Prominent pericholecystic fat stranding, with a large gallstone at the neck of the gallbladder. Right hemidiaphragmatic eventration with significant right middle or lower lobe atelectasis. Mild left lower lobe atelectasis. Prominent portacaval and celiac lymph nodes, likely reactive. 1.1 cm right hepatic cyst. No evidence of malignancy.
